233 static int32_t rangeProcHWA_ConfigEDMADummyThreeLinks
234 (
235  EDMA_Handle handle,
236  DPEDMA_3LinkChanCfg *chanCfg,
237  uint8_t chainChId0,
238  uint8_t chainChId1,
239  uint8_t chainChId2,
240  uint16_t numIter,
241  EDMA_transferCompletionCallbackFxn_t transferCompletionCallbackFxn,
242  uintptr_t transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg
243 )
244 {
245  EDMA_channelConfig_t config;
246  int32_t errorCode = EDMA_NO_ERROR;
247  uint16_t linkChId0;
248  uint16_t linkChId1;
249  uint16_t linkChId2;
250 
251  /* Get LinkChan from configuraiton */
252  linkChId0 = chanCfg->channelShadow[0];
253  linkChId1 = chanCfg->channelShadow[1];
254  linkChId2 = chanCfg->channelShadow[2];
255 
256  config.channelId = chanCfg->channel;
257  config.channelType = (uint8_t)EDMA3_CHANNEL_TYPE_DMA;
258  config.paramId = chanCfg->channel;
259  config.eventQueueId = chanCfg->eventQueue;
260 
261  config.paramSetConfig.sourceAddress = (uint32_t) NULL;
262  config.paramSetConfig.destinationAddress = (uint32_t) NULL;
263  config.paramSetConfig.bCountReload = 0;
264 
265  /* Hardware triggered dummy channel that runs for numIter loops */
266  config.paramSetConfig.aCount = 0;
267  config.paramSetConfig.bCount = numIter;
268  config.paramSetConfig.cCount = 0;
269 
270  config.paramSetConfig.sourceBindex = 0;
271  config.paramSetConfig.destinationBindex = 0;
272 
273  config.paramSetConfig.sourceCindex = 0;
274  config.paramSetConfig.destinationCindex = 0;
275 
276  config.paramSetConfig.linkAddress = EDMA_NULL_LINK_ADDRESS;
277  config.paramSetConfig.transferType = (uint8_t)EDMA3_SYNC_A;
278  config.paramSetConfig.transferCompletionCode = chainChId0;
279  config.paramSetConfig.sourceAddressingMode = (uint8_t) EDMA3_ADDRESSING_MODE_LINEAR;
280  config.paramSetConfig.destinationAddressingMode = (uint8_t) EDMA3_ADDRESSING_MODE_LINEAR;
281 
282  /* don't care because of linear addressing modes above */
283  config.paramSetConfig.fifoWidth = (uint8_t) EDMA3_FIFO_WIDTH_8BIT;
284  config.paramSetConfig.isStaticSet = false;
285  config.paramSetConfig.isEarlyCompletion = false;
286  config.paramSetConfig.isFinalTransferInterruptEnabled = false;
287  config.paramSetConfig.isIntermediateTransferInterruptEnabled = false;
288  config.paramSetConfig.isFinalChainingEnabled =true;
289  config.paramSetConfig.isIntermediateChainingEnabled =true;
290  config.transferCompletionCallbackFxn = NULL;
291 
292  if ((errorCode = EDMA_configChannel(handle, &config, true)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
293  {
294  goto exit;
295  }
296 
297  /* Change the parameter set to use different transferCompletionCode */
298  {
299  EDMA_paramConfig_t paramConfig;
300 
301  memcpy((void *)&paramConfig.paramSetConfig, (void *)&config.paramSetConfig, sizeof(EDMA_paramSetConfig_t));
302 
303  paramConfig.transferCompletionCallbackFxn = NULL;
304  paramConfig.transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg = NULL;
305 
306  /* to TX1 EDMA channel */
307  paramConfig.paramSetConfig.transferCompletionCode = chainChId2;
308  if ((errorCode = EDMA_configParamSet(handle, linkChId2, &paramConfig)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
309  {
310  goto exit;
311  }
312 
313  /* to TX2 EDMA channel */
314  paramConfig.paramSetConfig.transferCompletionCode = chainChId1;
315  if ((errorCode = EDMA_configParamSet(handle, linkChId1, &paramConfig)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
316  {
317  goto exit;
318  }
319 
320  /* to TX0 EDMA channel */
321  paramConfig.paramSetConfig.transferCompletionCode = chainChId0;
322  if ((errorCode = EDMA_configParamSet(handle, linkChId0, &paramConfig)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
323  {
324  goto exit;
325  }
326 
327  /* Link 3 shadow links */
328  if ((errorCode = EDMA_linkParamSets(handle, linkChId0, linkChId1)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
329  {
330  goto exit;
331  }
332 
333  if ((errorCode = EDMA_linkParamSets(handle, linkChId1, linkChId2)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
334  {
335  goto exit;
336  }
337 
338  if ((errorCode = EDMA_linkParamSets(handle, linkChId2, linkChId0)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
339  {
340  goto exit;
341  }
342 
343  /* Link dummy channel to the 2nd link */
344  if ((errorCode = EDMA_linkParamSets(handle, chanCfg->channel, linkChId1)) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
345  {
346  goto exit;
347  }
348  }
349 exit:
350  return(errorCode);
351 }

374 static int32_t rangeProcHWA_ConfigEDMATranspose
375 (
376  rangeProc_dpParams *dpParams,
377  EDMA_Handle handle,
378  DPEDMA_ChanCfg *chanCfg,
379  DPEDMA_ChainingCfg *chainingCfg,
380  uint32_t srcAddress,
381  uint32_t destAddress,
382  bool isTransferCompletionEnabled,
383  EDMA_transferCompletionCallbackFxn_t transferCompletionCallbackFxn,
384  uintptr_t transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg
385 )
386 {
387  DPEDMA_syncABCfg syncABCfg;
388  int32_t retVal;
389 
390  /* dpedma configuration */
391  syncABCfg.aCount = dpParams->numRxAntennas * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
392  syncABCfg.bCount = dpParams->numRangeBins;
393  syncABCfg.cCount = dpParams->numChirpsPerFrame/2U;
394  syncABCfg.srcBIdx = dpParams->numRxAntennas * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
395  syncABCfg.srcCIdx = 0U;
396  syncABCfg.dstBIdx = dpParams->numRxAntennas *dpParams->numChirpsPerFrame * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
397  syncABCfg.dstCIdx = dpParams->numRxAntennas * 2U * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
398 
399  syncABCfg.srcAddress = srcAddress;
400  syncABCfg.destAddress= destAddress;
401 
402  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncAB(handle,
403  chanCfg,
404  chainingCfg,
405  &syncABCfg,
406  true, /* isEventTriggered */
407  false, /* isIntermediateTransferCompletionEnabled */
408  isTransferCompletionEnabled, /* isTransferCompletionEnabled */
409  transferCompletionCallbackFxn,
410  transferCompletionCallbackFxnArg);
411 
412  if (retVal != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
413  {
414  goto exit;
415  }
416 
417 exit:
418  return (retVal);
419 }

435 static int32_t rangeProcHWA_ConfigHWACommon
436 (
437  rangeProcHWAObj *rangeProcObj
438 )
439 {
440  HWA_CommonConfig hwaCommonConfig;
441  rangeProc_dpParams *DPParams;
442  int32_t retVal;
443 
444  DPParams = &rangeProcObj->params;
445 
446  /***********************/
447  /* HWA COMMON CONFIG */
448  /***********************/
449  /* Config Common Registers */
450  hwaCommonConfig.configMask = HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_NUMLOOPS |
451  HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_PARAMSTARTIDX |
452  HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_PARAMSTOPIDX |
453  HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_FFT1DENABLE |
454  HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_INTERFERENCETHRESHOLD |
455  HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_TWIDDITHERENABLE |
456  HWA_COMMONCONFIG_MASK_LFSRSEED;
457 
458  hwaCommonConfig.fftConfig.twidDitherEnable = HWA_FEATURE_BIT_ENABLE;
459  hwaCommonConfig.fftConfig.lfsrSeed = 0x1234567; /*Some non-zero value*/
460  hwaCommonConfig.numLoops = DPParams->numChirpsPerFrame/2U;
461  hwaCommonConfig.paramStartIdx = rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx;
462  hwaCommonConfig.paramStopIdx = rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx + rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.numParamSet - 1U;
463 
464  if (rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.dataInputMode == DPU_RangeProcHWA_InputMode_ISOLATED)
465  {
466  /* HWA will input data from M0 memory*/
467  hwaCommonConfig.fftConfig.fft1DEnable = HWA_FEATURE_BIT_DISABLE;
468  }
469  else
470  {
471  /* HWA will input data from ADC buffer memory*/
472  hwaCommonConfig.fftConfig.fft1DEnable = HWA_FEATURE_BIT_ENABLE;
473  }
474  hwaCommonConfig.fftConfig.interferenceThreshold = 0xFFFFFF;
475  retVal = HWA_configCommon(rangeProcObj->initParms.hwaHandle, &hwaCommonConfig);
476  if (retVal != 0)
477  {
478  goto exit;
479  }
480 
481  /**********************************************/
482  /* ENABLE NUMLOOPS DONE INTERRUPT FROM HWA */
483  /**********************************************/
484  retVal = HWA_enableDoneInterrupt(rangeProcObj->initParms.hwaHandle,
485  rangeProcHWADoneIsrCallback,
486  rangeProcObj->hwaDoneSemaHandle);
487  if (retVal != 0)
488  {
489  goto exit;
490  }
491 
492 exit:
493  return(retVal);
494 }
515 static int32_t rangeProcHWA_ConfigHWA
516 (
517  rangeProcHWAObj *rangeProcObj,
518  uint8_t destChanPing,
519  uint8_t destChanPong,
520  uint16_t hwaMemSrcPingOffset,
521  uint16_t hwaMemSrcPongOffset,
522  uint16_t hwaMemDestPingOffset,
523  uint16_t hwaMemDestPongOffset
524 )
525 {
526  HWA_InterruptConfig paramISRConfig;
527  int32_t errCode = 0;
528  uint32_t paramsetIdx = 0;
529  uint32_t hwParamsetIdx;
530  uint32_t pingParamSetIdx = 0;
531  HWA_ParamConfig hwaParamCfg[DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_NUM_HWA_PARAM_SETS];
532  HWA_Handle hwaHandle;
533  rangeProc_dpParams *pDPParams;
534  uint8_t index;
535 
536  hwaHandle = rangeProcObj->initParms.hwaHandle;
537  pDPParams = &rangeProcObj->params;
538 
539  memset(hwaParamCfg,0,sizeof(hwaParamCfg));
540 
541  hwParamsetIdx = rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx;
542  for(index = 0; index < DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_NUM_HWA_PARAM_SETS; index++)
543  {
544  errCode = HWA_disableParamSetInterrupt(hwaHandle, index + rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx,
545  HWA_PARAMDONE_INTERRUPT_TYPE_CPU |HWA_PARAMDONE_INTERRUPT_TYPE_DMA);
546  if (errCode != 0)
547  {
548  goto exit;
549  }
550  }
551 
552  /***********************/
553  /* PING DUMMY PARAMSET */
554  /***********************/
555  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].triggerMode = HWA_TRIG_MODE_DMA;
556  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dmaTriggerSrc = hwParamsetIdx;
557  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelMode = HWA_ACCELMODE_NONE;
558  errCode = HWA_configParamSet(hwaHandle,
559  hwParamsetIdx,
560  &hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx],NULL);
561  if (errCode != 0)
562  {
563  goto exit;
564  }
565 
566  /***********************/
567  /* PING PROCESS PARAMSET */
568  /***********************/
569  paramsetIdx++;
570  hwParamsetIdx++;
571  pingParamSetIdx = paramsetIdx;
572 
573  /* adcbuf mapped */
574  if(rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.dataInputMode == DPU_RangeProcHWA_InputMode_MAPPED)
575  {
576  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].triggerMode = HWA_TRIG_MODE_DFE;
577  }
578  else
579  {
580  /*adcbuf not mapped, should trigger after edma copy is done */
581  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].triggerMode = HWA_TRIG_MODE_DMA;
582  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dmaTriggerSrc = hwParamsetIdx;
583  }
584 
585  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelMode = HWA_ACCELMODE_FFT;
586  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAddr = hwaMemSrcPingOffset;
587 
588  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcShift = 0;
589  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcCircShiftWrap = 0;
590  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcRealComplex = HWA_SAMPLES_FORMAT_COMPLEX;
591  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcWidth = HWA_SAMPLES_WIDTH_16BIT;
592  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcSign = HWA_SAMPLES_SIGNED;
593  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcConjugate = 0;
594  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcScale = 8;
595  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.bpmEnable = 0;
596  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.bpmPhase = 0;
597  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAddr = hwaMemDestPingOffset;
598 
599  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstRealComplex = HWA_SAMPLES_FORMAT_COMPLEX;
600  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstWidth = HWA_SAMPLES_WIDTH_16BIT;
601  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstSign = HWA_SAMPLES_SIGNED;
602  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstConjugate = 0;
603  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstScale = 0;
604  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstSkipInit = 0;
605 
606  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.fftEn = 1;
607  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.fftSize = mathUtils_ceilLog2(pDPParams->numRangeBins);
608  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.butterflyScaling = 0x3;
609  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.interfZeroOutEn = 0;
610  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.windowEn = 1;
611  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.windowStart = rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.hwaWinRamOffset;
612  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.winSymm = rangeProcObj->hwaCfg.hwaWinSym;
613  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.winInterpolateMode = 0;
614  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.magLogEn = HWA_FFT_MODE_MAGNITUDE_LOG2_DISABLED;
615  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].accelModeArgs.fftMode.fftOutMode = HWA_FFT_MODE_OUTPUT_DEFAULT;
616  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].complexMultiply.mode = HWA_COMPLEX_MULTIPLY_MODE_DISABLE;
617 
618  /* HWA range FFT src/dst configuration*/
619  if(rangeProcObj->interleave == DPIF_RXCHAN_INTERLEAVE_MODE)
620  {
621  if(rangeProcObj->radarCubeLayout == rangeProc_dataLayout_RANGE_DOPPLER_TxAnt_RxAnt)
622  {
623  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAcnt = pDPParams->numAdcSamples - 1; /* this is samples - 1 */
624  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAIdx = pDPParams->numRxAntennas* sizeof(uint32_t);
625  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcBcnt = pDPParams->numRxAntennas-1;
626  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcBIdx = sizeof(uint32_t);
627 
628  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAcnt = pDPParams->numRangeBins-1;
629  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAIdx = pDPParams->numRxAntennas * sizeof(uint32_t);
630  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstBIdx = sizeof(uint32_t);
631  }
632  else
633  {
634  /* Other radarCube layout format is not supported */
635  errCode = DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_ENOTIMPL;
636  goto exit;
637  }
638  }
639  else
640  {
641  if(rangeProcObj->radarCubeLayout == rangeProc_dataLayout_RANGE_DOPPLER_TxAnt_RxAnt)
642  {
643  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAcnt = pDPParams->numAdcSamples - 1;
644  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAIdx = sizeof(uint32_t);
645  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcBcnt = pDPParams->numRxAntennas-1;
646  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcBIdx = rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset;
647 
648  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAcnt = pDPParams->numRangeBins-1;
649  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAIdx = sizeof(uint32_t) * pDPParams->numRxAntennas;
650  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstBIdx = sizeof(uint32_t);
651  }
652  else
653  {
654  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAcnt = pDPParams->numAdcSamples - 1;
655  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcAIdx = sizeof(uint32_t);
656  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcBcnt = pDPParams->numRxAntennas-1;
657  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].source.srcBIdx = rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset;
658  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAcnt = pDPParams->numRangeBins-1;
659  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstAIdx = sizeof(uint32_t);
660  hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx].dest.dstBIdx = pDPParams->numRangeBins * sizeof(uint32_t);
661  }
662  }
663 
664  errCode = HWA_configParamSet(hwaHandle,
665  hwParamsetIdx,
666  &hwaParamCfg[paramsetIdx],NULL);
667  if (errCode != 0)
668  {
669  goto exit;
670  }
671 
672  /* enable the DMA hookup to this paramset so that data gets copied out */
673  paramISRConfig.interruptTypeFlag = HWA_PARAMDONE_INTERRUPT_TYPE_DMA;
674  paramISRConfig.dma.dstChannel = destChanPing;
675 
676  errCode = HWA_enableParamSetInterrupt(hwaHandle,hwParamsetIdx,&paramISRConfig);
677  if (errCode != 0)
678  {
679  goto exit;
680  }
681 
682  /***********************/
683  /* PONG DUMMY PARAMSET */
684  /***********************/
685  paramsetIdx++;
686  hwParamsetIdx++;
687

1597 static void rangeProcHWA_dcRangeSignatureCompensation
1598 (
1599  rangeProcHWAObj *obj
1600 )
1601 {
1602  uint32_t antIdx, rngBinIdx;
1603  uint32_t ind;
1604  int32_t dcRangeSigMeanSize;
1605  uint32_t doppIdx;
1606  cmplx16ImRe_t *fftOut1D;
1607  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg *calibDc = &obj->calibDcRangeSigCfg;
1608  int32_t negativeBinIdx = calibDc->negativeBinIdx;
1609  int32_t positiveBinIdx = calibDc->positiveBinIdx;
1610  cmplx32ImRe_t *dcRangeSigMean = obj->dcRangeSigMean;
1611  rangeProc_dpParams *dpParams;
1612 
1613  dpParams = &obj->params;
1614  fftOut1D = (cmplx16ImRe_t *) obj->radarCubebuf;
1615 
1616  dcRangeSigMeanSize = dpParams->numVirtualAntennas * (positiveBinIdx - negativeBinIdx + 1);
1617  if (obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr == 0)
1618  {
1619  memset(dcRangeSigMean, 0, dcRangeSigMeanSize * sizeof(cmplx32ImRe_t));
1620  }
1621 
1622  /* RadarCube FMT2 */
1623  if(obj->radarCubeLayout == rangeProc_dataLayout_RANGE_DOPPLER_TxAnt_RxAnt)
1624  {
1625  int32_t rngOffset;
1626  int32_t numVirtAnt;
1627 
1628  numVirtAnt = dpParams->numVirtualAntennas;
1629 
1630  rngOffset = dpParams->numVirtualAntennas * dpParams->numDopplerChirps;
1631  /* Calibration */
1632  if (obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr < calibDc->numAvgChirps)
1633  {
1634  for (doppIdx = 0; doppIdx < dpParams->numDopplerChirps; doppIdx++)
1635  {
1636  /* Accumulate */
1637  ind = 0;
1638  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx <= positiveBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1639  {
1640  for (antIdx = 0; antIdx < numVirtAnt; antIdx++)
1641  {
1642  int32_t binIdx = rngBinIdx * rngOffset + doppIdx * numVirtAnt + antIdx;
1643  dcRangeSigMean[ind].real += fftOut1D[binIdx].real;
1644  dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag += fftOut1D[binIdx].imag;
1645  ind++;
1646  }
1647  }
1648  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx < -negativeBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1649  {
1650  for (antIdx = 0; antIdx < numVirtAnt; antIdx++)
1651  {
1652  int32_t binIdx = (dpParams->numRangeBins + negativeBinIdx + rngBinIdx) * rngOffset +
1653  doppIdx * numVirtAnt + antIdx;
1654  dcRangeSigMean[ind].real += fftOut1D[binIdx].real;
1655  dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag += fftOut1D[binIdx].imag;
1656  ind++;
1657  }
1658  }
1659  obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr++;
1660  }
1661 
1662  if (obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr == calibDc->numAvgChirps)
1663  {
1664  /* Divide */
1665  for (ind = 0; ind < dcRangeSigMeanSize; ind++)
1666  {
1667  dcRangeSigMean[ind].real = dcRangeSigMean[ind].real >> obj->calibDcNumLog2AvgChirps;
1668  dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag = dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag >> obj->calibDcNumLog2AvgChirps;
1669  }
1670  }
1671  }
1672  else
1673  {
1674  /* fftOut1D -= dcRangeSigMean */
1675  for (doppIdx = 0; doppIdx < dpParams->numDopplerChirps; doppIdx++)
1676  {
1677  ind = 0;
1678  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx <= positiveBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1679  {
1680  for (antIdx = 0; antIdx < numVirtAnt; antIdx++)
1681  {
1682  int32_t binIdx = rngBinIdx * rngOffset + doppIdx * numVirtAnt + antIdx;
1683 
1684  fftOut1D[binIdx].real -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].real;
1685  fftOut1D[binIdx].imag -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag;
1686  ind++;
1687  }
1688  }
1689  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx < -negativeBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1690  {
1691  for (antIdx = 0; antIdx < numVirtAnt; antIdx++)
1692  {
1693  int32_t binIdx = (dpParams->numRangeBins + negativeBinIdx + rngBinIdx) * rngOffset +
1694  doppIdx * numVirtAnt + antIdx;
1695  fftOut1D[binIdx].real -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].real;
1696  fftOut1D[binIdx].imag -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag;
1697  ind++;
1698  }
1699  }
1700  }
1701  }
1702  }
1703  else
1704  {
1705  /* RadarCube FMT1 */
1706  uint32_t txAntIdx;
1707  uint32_t rxAntIdx;
1708  int32_t txAntOffset;
1709  int32_t dopOffset;
1710 
1711  /* FMT1: cmplx16ImRe_t x[numTXPatterns][numDopplerChirps][numRX][numRangeBins] |1D Range FFT output*/
1712  txAntOffset = dpParams->numRxAntennas * dpParams->numDopplerChirps * dpParams->numRangeBins;
1713  dopOffset = dpParams->numRxAntennas * dpParams->numRangeBins;
1714 
1715  /* Calibration */
1716  if (obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr < calibDc->numAvgChirps)
1717  {
1718  for (doppIdx = 0; doppIdx < dpParams->numDopplerChirps; doppIdx++)
1719  {
1720  /* Accumulate for all doppler bins */
1721  ind = 0;
1722 
1723  for(txAntIdx = 0; txAntIdx< dpParams->numTxAntennas; txAntIdx++)
1724  {
1725  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx <= positiveBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1726  {
1727  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < dpParams->numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
1728  {
1729  int32_t binIdx = txAntIdx * txAntOffset + doppIdx * dopOffset +
1730  dpParams->numRangeBins *rxAntIdx +
1731  rngBinIdx;
1732  dcRangeSigMean[ind].real += fftOut1D[binIdx].real;
1733  dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag += fftOut1D[binIdx].imag;
1734  ind++;
1735  }
1736  }
1737  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx < -negativeBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1738  {
1739  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < dpParams->numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
1740  {
1741  int32_t binIdx = txAntIdx * txAntOffset + doppIdx * dopOffset +
1742  dpParams->numRangeBins *rxAntIdx +
1743  (dpParams->numRangeBins + negativeBinIdx + rngBinIdx);
1744 
1745  dcRangeSigMean[ind].real += fftOut1D[binIdx].real;
1746  dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag += fftOut1D[binIdx].imag;
1747  ind++;
1748  }
1749  }
1750  }
1751  obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr++;
1752  }
1753 
1754  if (obj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr == calibDc->numAvgChirps)
1755  {
1756  /* Divide */
1757  for (ind = 0; ind < dcRangeSigMeanSize; ind++)
1758  {
1759  dcRangeSigMean[ind].real = dcRangeSigMean[ind].real >> obj->calibDcNumLog2AvgChirps;
1760  dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag = dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag >> obj->calibDcNumLog2AvgChirps;
1761  }
1762  }
1763  }
1764  else
1765  {
1766  /* fftOut1D -= dcRangeSigMean */
1767  for (doppIdx = 0; doppIdx < dpParams->numDopplerChirps; doppIdx++)
1768  {
1769  ind = 0;
1770  for(txAntIdx = 0; txAntIdx< dpParams->numTxAntennas; txAntIdx++)
1771  {
1772  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx <= positiveBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1773  {
1774  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < dpParams->numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
1775  {
1776  int32_t binIdx = txAntIdx * txAntOffset + doppIdx * dopOffset +
1777  dpParams->numRangeBins *rxAntIdx +
1778  rngBinIdx;
1779  fftOut1D[binIdx].real -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].real;
1780  fftOut1D[binIdx].imag -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag;
1781  ind++;
1782  }
1783  }
1784  for (rngBinIdx = 0; rngBinIdx < -negativeBinIdx; rngBinIdx++)
1785  {
1786  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < dpParams->numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
1787  {
1788  int32_t binIdx = txAntIdx * txAntOffset + doppIdx * dopOffset +
1789  dpParams->numRangeBins *rxAntIdx +
1790  (dpParams->numRangeBins + negativeBinIdx + rngBinIdx);
1791  fftOut1D[binIdx].real -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].real;
1792  fftOut1D[binIdx].imag -= dcRangeSigMean[ind].imag;
1793  ind++;
1794  }
1795  }
1796  }
1797  }
1798  }
1799  }

1816 static int32_t rangeProcHWA_ParseConfig
1817 (
1818  rangeProcHWAObj *rangeProcObj,
1819  DPU_RangeProcHWA_Config *pConfigIn
1820 )
1821 {
1822  int32_t retVal = 0;
1823  rangeProc_dpParams *params;
1824  DPU_RangeProcHWA_StaticConfig *pStaticCfg;
1825 
1826  /* Get configuration pointers */
1827  pStaticCfg = &pConfigIn->staticCfg;
1828  params = &rangeProcObj->params;
1829 
1830  /* Save datapath parameters */
1831  params->numTxAntennas = pStaticCfg->numTxAntennas;
1832  params->numRxAntennas = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numRxAntennas;
1833  params->numVirtualAntennas = pStaticCfg->numVirtualAntennas;
1834  params->numChirpsPerChirpEvent = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numChirpsPerChirpEvent;
1835  params->numAdcSamples = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numAdcSamples;
1836  params->numRangeBins = pStaticCfg->numRangeBins;
1837  params->numChirpsPerFrame = pStaticCfg->numChirpsPerFrame;
1838  params->numDopplerChirps = pStaticCfg->numChirpsPerFrame/pStaticCfg->numTxAntennas;
1839 
1840  /* Save buffers */
1841  rangeProcObj->ADCdataBuf = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.data;
1842  rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)pConfigIn->hwRes.radarCube.data;
1843 
1844  /* Save interleave mode from ADCBuf configuraiton */
1845  rangeProcObj->interleave = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.interleave;
1846 
1847  if((rangeProcObj->interleave ==DPIF_RXCHAN_NON_INTERLEAVE_MODE) &&
1848  (rangeProcObj->params.numRxAntennas > 1) )
1849  {
1850  /* For rangeProcDPU needs rx channel has same offset from one channel to the next channel
1851  Use first two channel offset to calculate the BIdx for EDMA
1852  */
1853  rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.rxChanOffset[1] -
1854  pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.rxChanOffset[0];
1855 
1856  /* rxChanOffset should be 16 bytes aligned and should be big enough to hold numAdcSamples */
1857  if ((rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset < (rangeProcObj->params.numAdcSamples * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t))) ||
1858  ((rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset & 0xF) != 0))
1859  {
1860  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_EADCBUF_INTF;
1861  goto exit;
1862  }
1863  }
1864 
1865  /* Save RadarCube format */
1866  if (pConfigIn->hwRes.radarCube.datafmt == DPIF_RADARCUBE_FORMAT_2)
1867  {
1868  rangeProcObj->radarCubeLayout = rangeProc_dataLayout_RANGE_DOPPLER_TxAnt_RxAnt;
1869  }
1870  else if(pConfigIn->hwRes.radarCube.datafmt == DPIF_RADARCUBE_FORMAT_1)
1871  {
1872  rangeProcObj->radarCubeLayout = rangeProc_dataLayout_TxAnt_DOPPLER_RxAnt_RANGE;
1873  }
1874  else
1875  {
1876  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_EINTERNAL;
1877  goto exit;
1878  }
1879 
1880  /* The following case can not be handled with the current 1TX EDMA scheme, reason is the Bindex exceeds what EDMA can handle. */
1881  if( (params->numRangeBins == 1024U) &&
1882  (params->numTxAntennas == 1U) &&
1883  (params->numRxAntennas == 4U) &&
1884  (rangeProcObj->radarCubeLayout == rangeProc_dataLayout_TxAnt_DOPPLER_RxAnt_RANGE) )
1885  {
1886  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_ENOTIMPL;
1887  goto exit;
1888  }
1889 
1890  /* The following case can not be handled with the current 3TX EDMA scheme, reason is the Bindex exceeds what EDMA(jump index<32768) can handle. */
1891  if( (params->numRangeBins == 1024U) &&
1892  (params->numTxAntennas == 3U) &&
1893  (params->numRxAntennas == 4U) &&
1894  (rangeProcObj->radarCubeLayout == rangeProc_dataLayout_TxAnt_DOPPLER_RxAnt_RANGE) )
1895  {
1896  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_ENOTIMPL;
1897  goto exit;
1898  }
1899 
1900  /* Prepare internal hardware resouces = trigger source matchs its paramset index */
1901  rangeProcObj->dataInTrigger[0] = 1U + pConfigIn->hwRes.hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx;
1902  rangeProcObj->dataInTrigger[1] = 3U + pConfigIn->hwRes.hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx;
1903  rangeProcObj->dataOutTrigger[0] = 0U + pConfigIn->hwRes.hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx;
1904  rangeProcObj->dataOutTrigger[1] = 2U + pConfigIn->hwRes.hwaCfg.paramSetStartIdx;
1905 
1906  /* Save hardware resources that will be used at runtime */
1907  rangeProcObj->edmaHandle= pConfigIn->hwRes.edmaHandle;
1908  rangeProcObj->dataOutSignatureChan = pConfigIn->hwRes.edmaOutCfg.dataOutSignature.channel;
1909  rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean = pConfigIn->hwRes.dcRangeSigMean;
1910  rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMeanSize = pConfigIn->hwRes.dcRangeSigMeanSize;
1911  memcpy((void *)&rangeProcObj->hwaCfg, (void *)&pConfigIn->hwRes.hwaCfg, sizeof(DPU_RangeProcHWA_HwaConfig));
1912 
1913 exit:
1914  return(retVal);
1915 }

1992

1994

1998  *errCode = DPU_RANGEPROCHWA_EINVAL;

2014

2017  if (*errCode < 0)
2018  {

2021 
2022  for (index = 0; index < hwaMemInfo.numBanks; index++)
2023  {
2024  rangeProcObj->hwaMemBankAddr[index] = hwaMemInfo.baseAddress + index * hwaMemInfo.bankSize;
2025  }

2028  SemaphoreP_Params_init(&semParams);
